In this statement, President Obama acknowledges the 63rd anniversary of Israel's independence and highlights the strong bond between the United States and Israel. He expresses confidence in the growing relationship between the two countries and their shared commitment to Israel's security. The President also recognizes the ongoing changes in the Middle East and North Africa, expressing hope for a more peaceful and prosperous region where people can fulfill their aspirations. He reiterates the United States' dedication to working with Israel and others towards a comprehensive peace, including a two-state solution. Finally, President Obama extends his best wishes to President Peres, Prime Minister Netanyahu, and the people of Israel on their Independence Day.